All,

A flange came off of one of our Rev ion 90 degree gearbox bearings and it has ceased up.  With the limited supply right now we need that box back up and running.  Does anyone know where to source the bearings for it?  REV does not sell them on their site.  (I have sent them an email).  They seem to be 17mm ID, 26 mm OD, 5mm Thick and flanged.  The only ones I saw at our normal places like McMaster are super expensive.

Thanks for any help in advance!

Greg
Is this the gearbox? If so, the onshape model says there are 3 of the F6803ZZ bearings and one 6801ZZ bearing.

posts.name: NathanNFM
posts.cooked: Just a note to help when looking for bearings, “Z” indicates a shield and “RS” indicates a seal. A “2Z” or “ZZ” indicates that there are two shields, one on each side, but often each individual shield will only have one “Z” stamped on it, as it has no way of knowing if it’s partner shield is actually present. The same goes for “RS” and 2RS". Theoretically (I have never seen one in person) you could have a bearing that was open on one side and shielded or sealed on the other and that would be just a single “Z” or “RS”. Also, a leading “F” is for Flanged.
